title: For Sale:  Colt Army Special
postcontent: Colt Army Special in .38 Special. Great piece of history; this particular revolver was produced in 1912, according to Colt's online serial number lookup.This will shoot off-the-shelf .38 Special ammo (but not +P ammo).Colt named these revolvers the Army because they hoped to get an Army contract. Little did they know the Army had already settled on the .45. Several of these pistols did see military service, though, especially among air crews and naval officers in World War II (when Smith and Wesson couldn't keep up). After the war, this same pistol was renamed the Official Police and became a favorite of police departments across the country.
